Since it seems that there are some users around,

	OCamlBrowser 1.06 has been released


OCamlBrowser is simply a modified version of LablBrowser such that you
can use it with standard O'Caml in place of O'Labl. For details see:

	http://wwwfun.kurims.kyoto-u.ac.jp/soft/olabl/

The only difficulty is that you will need O'Labl to compile it. 
As a result it is not intended for individual users (they should
prefer O'Labl, which is source compatible with O'Caml), but rather for
places where standard O'Caml has to be used, as a tool for students
for instance.

Sources of OCamlBrowser can be obtained from:

   ftp://ftp.kurims.kyoto-u.ac.jp/pub/lang/olabl/ocamlbrowser-1.06.tar.gz

